GOMBE â€“ The exit from the Gombe State chapter of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) by one of its stalwarts, Dr Jamilu Isyaku Gwamna, is eliciting applause and excitement from his supporters. Many of them had earlier been appealing to him to leave the APC because they allege that they will not get justice from the APC party, especially as The Governor had pocketed all the executive members in the entire State. Dr Jamilu, a former Governorship aspirant in PDP before the 2019 general election, who dumped the PDP after the primaries with thousands of his supporters, says his sojourn in the APC has come to an end. Euro Surges As Record Inflation Adds Pressure On ECB Court Adjourns Hearing Of $130m Suit Against SAIPEM The chieftain has therefore tendered his resignation from being a member of the APC in Gombe State through the APC Ward chairman of Jekadafari ward on Tuesday, 1st February 2022. In the resignation letter, a copy which was made available to our correspondent, Gwamna explained that he made the decision after wide consultation with his family, political associates and supporters. Although he did not state reasons for dumping the party, his supporters who spoke with our correspondent alleged that APC leadership in the state has taken side with the incumbent Governor of the state Alhaji Muhammad Inuwa Yahaya. He did not also state his next political direction but speculations are rife that he may be returning to the PDP. One of the close supporters of Gwamna, Isa Kaltungo, said in some Local Government Areas visited by Governor Yahaya, some stakeholders and party executives flagrantly endorsed the governor for the second time, a situation that does not augur well for the party. POLL According to him, that was an indication that the party would not provide a fair playing ground for all Governorship aspirants in the next primary elections.